news.title: Will hand over keys of houses to 1 lakh poor people in UP within 100 days: Deputy CM
news.para: The state government will also constitute 50,000 new self-help groups under the State Rural Livelihood Mission to augment women's income in rural areas within the same time period, he told PTI in an interview here.v

news.title: RBI extends rationalised home loan norms till March 2023
news.para: In October 2020, the Reserve Bank as a countercyclical measure to deal with the COVID situation had rationalised the risk weights by linking them only with Loan to Value (LTV) ratios for all new housing loans sanctioned up to March 31, 2022.

news.title: Chandigarh: Unearned profit on property down from 33.33% to 25%
news.para: Unearned profit is defined as the difference between the price paid by the original allottee and the market value of the property at the time of transfer.

news.title: Karnataka likely to continue 10% cut on property guidance value for another three months
news.para: "I had earlier slashed the property guidance value by 10 percent for three months....it was for the benefit of the people, there has been good response to it from across the state. We have been able to generate Rs 1,300 crore more revenue than the set target of Rs 12,000 crore," Ashoka said.

news.title: Gurugram: Illegal colony being built in Bandhwari demolished
news.para: The developer was building a road network, damp-proof courses, boundary walls and some buildings in the area. A team led by MCG assistant engineer Waseem Akram demolished them.

news.title: Rajasthan government initiates move to issue lease deeds to Nazul plot owners
news.para: The move has been initiated as the state government plans to issue lease deeds to plot owners whose colonies are developed on government land (Sawai Chak) and Nazul land during Shahar-2021 campaign.

news.title: Kolkata: At 4,697, property registration jumps three times in March
news.para: According to the Directorate of Registrations and Stamp Revenue, 4,697 property sales deeds were registered last month, up from 1,593 registered in previous month.

news.title: No decision yet on hike in property tax in Secunderabad
news.para: SCB chief executive officer, B Ajith Reddy, who moved this proposal, said that the total consolidated tax rate is 24.6% on residential buildings and 27.6% on commercial buildings.

news.title: RBI keeps repo rate unchanged at 4%
news.para: The monetary policy committee held the lending rate, or the repo rate, at 4%. The reverse repo rate , or the key borrowing rate, was also kept unchanged at 3.35%.

news.title: Chandigarh: Test launch of online building plan approval system
news.para: In the meeting, technical scrutiny of online process for above 2 kanal residential building plan was examined. The consultant has been advised to simplify the process for making it more public friendly and ensure that there should be no human interface in this process of plan scrutiny.

news.title: Delhi: DDA launches phase-II for 5,382 in situ flats in Kalkaji slums
news.para: DDA had taken up in situ slum redevelopment of three clusters in Kalkaji Extension — Bhoomiheen Camp, Navjeevan Camp and Jawaharlal Nehru Camp.

news.title: Maharashtra: MMR notification for societies comes under flak
news.para: The move has come under flak. As per rules, administrators cannot take policy decisions such as redevelopment and major refurbishments except for day-to-day maintenance.

news.title: Gurugram: FIRs against 12 in DLF-3 for illegal construction
news.para: The DTCP has recommended FIRs against 50 property owners of three blocks — S, U and V — of DLF-3 for allegedly carrying out unauthorised construction in violation of the building code.

news.title: Housing demand up 6.7% in Q1, supply remains stable: Magicbricks Report
news.para: Mumbai with 15.2% rise, Gurugram 9.6%, Noida 8.2% and Delhi 5.6% witnessed highest sequential growth in demand, while Greater Noida with 6%, Mumbai 3.8%, Ahmedabad 3.2%, and Chennai 2.9% exhibited maximum growth in supply.

news.title: Mumbai: HDIL promoter gets bail in money laundering case
news.para: ​It is alleged that HDIL promoters Rakesh Wadhawan and his son Sarang, along with others, conspired to cheat PMC Bank with the help of its former office bearers. Sarang will remain in jail as he is accused in other cases.
